The GPLv3 can be found in the `licenses` folder as `gpl-3.0.txt`.

- <https://github.com/YiCAX/YiCAD/tree/main/licenses>
- <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt>

### History ###

YiCAD contains code derived from QCAD Community Edition.

QCAD community edition version 2.0.5.0 was released under the GPLv2.

- <https://github.com/qcad/qcad>

YiCAD incorporates portions of QCAD Community Edition code,
translations, and resources. These portions retain their original copyright
notices and are distributed under the GPLv3 as required by their upstream
licensing. Modifications and additions by YiCAD are also released under
the GPLv3.

YiCAD has no official affiliation with the QCAD project.
The use of their code is subject to the terms of the GNU General Public
License version 3.

### Obtaining corresponding source ###

Complete corresponding source code for YiCAD is available from the
project repository:

- <https://github.com/YiCAX/YiCAD>

For tagged releases, source archives can be obtained at:

- <https://github.com/YiCAX/YiCAD/releases>

### Licenses of bundled content ###

The YiCAD source code is released as a whole under the GPLv3.
The following refers to the licenses used by bundled resources,
when they were released independently from YiCAD.

SARibbonBar is released under the MIT License.

- <https://github.com/czyt1988/SARibbon>

muparser is released under the BSD 2-Clause License.

- <https://github.com/beltoforion/muparser>

nlohmann/json is released under the MIT License.

- <https://github.com/nlohmann/json>

GLM is released under the MIT License.

- <https://github.com/g-truc/glm>

Qt 5.15 is available under the LGPLv3 or commercial license.
Users must install Qt separately and comply with its license terms.

- <https://www.qt.io>

Boost libraries are released under the Boost Software License 1.0.

- <https://www.boost.org/>

Eigen is released under the MPL2 and other compatible licenses.

- <https://eigen.tuxfamily.org>

GLEW is released under the MIT License and the Modified BSD License.

- <https://github.com/nigels-com/glew>

FreeType is released under the FreeType License (FTL) or GPLv2.

- <https://www.freetype.org>

zlib is released under the zlib License.

- <https://www.zlib.net>

CGAL is released under the GPLv3+ or LGPLv3+ (dual-licensed).

- <https://www.cgal.org>

GMP (GNU Multiple Precision Arithmetic Library) is released under the LGPLv3+.

- <https://gmplib.org>

pugixml is released under the MIT License.

- <https://pugixml.org>

Third-party components not listed above are distributed under their
respective licenses. See the `licenses` directory for details.
